%pyspark
sc.addFile("hdfs://big0.iie.org.mx:9000/JSGP/datasets/london/utils/fireTS/core.py")
sc.addFile("hdfs://big0.iie.org.mx:9000/JSGP/datasets/london/utils/fireTS/utils.py")
sc.addFile("hdfs://big0.iie.org.mx:9000/JSGP/datasets/london/utils/fireTS/models.py")

import utils
import core
import models
from models import NARX, DirectAutoRegressor
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import os
from pyspark.sql import functions as sqlFunctions
from pyspark.sql.window import Window
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import re
import matplotlib.dates as mdates
from pyspark.ml.evaluation import RegressionEvaluator

%pyspark

#Select meter to forecast
#meters=["MAC000003","MAC000007","MAC000008","MAC000030","MAC000031","MAC000128","MAC003686","MAC005455"]
#meters=meters_db.select("METER_ID").toPandas()
meters0=meter_weather_1h.select("METER_ID").toPandas()
meters2=pd.DataFrame(meters0["METER_ID"].unique(),columns=['METER_ID'] )
meters=meters2['METER_ID'].values.tolist()
# Number of experiments to run
n_exp=3

# Percentaje of data used to train
perc=0.80

%pyspark
ct=0
columns = ['METER_ID','R2_NARX','RMSE_NARX', 'MSE_NARX', 'MAE_NARX','R2_DAR','RMSE_DAR', 'MSE_DAR', 'MAE_DAR']
metrics_meter = pd.DataFrame(columns=columns)

for meter in meters:
    
    print("\nMETER "+meter)
    
    #From dataframe generated at analytics_data notebook
    data0=meter_weather_1h.filter(col("METER_ID")==meter)
    data1=data0.toPandas()
    print (len(data1))
    if (len(data1)>=8000):
        
        data = data1.set_index('TIMESTAMP')
        data.index = pd.to_datetime(data.index)
        data=data.sort_values(by=['METER_ID', "TIMESTAMP"])
        porc_train=int(perc*len(data))
        ytrain = data['ENERGY'].iloc[:porc_train]
        Xtrain = data.loc[:, ['TEMPERATURE']].iloc[:porc_train, :]

        ytest = data['ENERGY'].iloc[porc_train:-1]
        Xtest = data.loc[:, ['TEMPERATURE']].iloc[porc_train:-1, :]
		
    	# NARX with Random Forest and grid seach for hyperparameter tuning
        r2_win_narx=0
        model_win_narx=NARX(RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=15), auto_order=24, exog_order=[24], exog_delay=[1])
    
    
        for i in range(n_exp):
		
            narx_mdl = NARX(RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=15), auto_order=24, exog_order=[24], exog_delay=[1])
            para_grid = {'n_estimators': [1, 5, 10]}
            narx_mdl.grid_search(Xtrain, ytrain, para_grid, verbose=0)
            narx_mdl.fit(Xtrain, ytrain)
            ypred = narx_mdl.predict(Xtest, ytest, step=1)
            ypred = pd.Series(ypred, index=ytest.index)

            results=pd.DataFrame({'TIMESTAMP':ypred.index, 'prediction':ypred.values, 'label':ytest.values})
            results_df=spark.createDataFrame(results)  
            results_df=results_df.filter(~(isnan(results_df["prediction"])))
            evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="r2")
            r2 = evaluator.evaluate(results_df)
        
        
		    #print("Run %d - R2 = %f" % (i, r2))
		
            if r2>r2_win_narx:
                r2_win_narx=r2
                evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="rmse")
                rmse_win_narx = evaluator.evaluate(results_df)
                evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="mse")
                mse_win_narx = evaluator.evaluate(results_df)
                evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="mae")
                mae_win_narx = evaluator.evaluate(results_df)
                model_win_narx=narx_mdl
                y_pred_win=ypred
                winner_exp=i
                results_win_narx=results
                results_win_narx_df=results_df
        
        print("Best model for NARX found at experiment %d - R2=%f" %(winner_exp,r2_win_narx))
        #print("Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE) on test data = %g" % rmse_win_narx)
        #print("Mean Squared Error (MSE) on test data = %g" % mse_win_narx)
        #print("Mean Absolute Error (MAE) on test data = %g" % mae_win_narx)
        #print("R2 coefficient (R2) on test data = %g" % r2_win_narx)

        results_narx=results_win_narx_df.withColumn("R2",lit(r2_win_narx)).withColumn("RMSE",lit(rmse_win_narx))
        results_narx=results_narx.select(row_number().over(Window().orderBy("TIMESTAMP")).alias("ID"), col("*"))
        results_narx.write.format("com.databricks.spark.csv").option("header", "true").save("hdfs://big0.iie.org.mx:9000/JSGP/datasets/london/analytics/forecasting/meters/narx/"+meter+".csv")
    
        # Direct Auto Regressor with Random Forest and grid search for hyperparameter tuning
        r2_win_dar=0
        model_win_dar=DirectAutoRegressor(RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=15), auto_order=24, exog_order=[24], exog_delay=[1], pred_step=1)
    
        
        for i in range(n_exp):
		
		
            dar_mdl = DirectAutoRegressor(RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=15), auto_order=24, exog_order=[24], exog_delay=[1], pred_step=1)
            para_grid = {'n_estimators': [1, 5, 10]}
            dar_mdl.grid_search(Xtrain, ytrain, para_grid, verbose=0)
            dar_mdl.fit(Xtrain, ytrain)
            ypred = dar_mdl.predict(Xtest, ytest)
            ypred = pd.Series(ypred, index=ytest.index)

		
            results=pd.DataFrame({'TIMESTAMP':ypred.index, 'prediction':ypred.values, 'label':ytest.values})
            results_df=spark.createDataFrame(results)  
            results_df=results_df.filter(~(isnan(results_df["prediction"])))
            evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="r2")
            r2 = evaluator.evaluate(results_df)
    		#print("Run %d - R2 = %f" % (i, r2))
		
            if r2>r2_win_dar:
                r2_win_dar=r2
                evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="rmse")
                rmse_win_dar = evaluator.evaluate(results_df)
                evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="mse")
                mse_win_dar = evaluator.evaluate(results_df)
                evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", metricName="mae")
                mae_win_dar = evaluator.evaluate(results_df)
            
                model_win_dar=dar_mdl
                y_pred_win=ypred
                winner_exp=i
                results_win_dar=results
                results_win_dar_df=results_df
    
    
        print("Best model for DAR found at experiment %d - R2=%f" %(winner_exp,r2_win_dar))
        #print("Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE) on test data = %g" % rmse_win_dar)
        #print("Mean Squared Error (MSE) on test data = %g" % mse_win_dar)
        #print("Mean Absolute Error (MAE) on test data = %g" % mae_win_dar)
        #print("R2 coefficient (R2) on test data = %g" % r2_win_dar)

        results_dar=results_win_dar_df.withColumn("R2",lit(r2_win_dar)).withColumn("RMSE",lit(rmse_win_dar))
        results_dar=results_dar.select(row_number().over(Window().orderBy("TIMESTAMP")).alias("ID"), col("*"))
        results_dar.write.format("com.databricks.spark.csv").option("header", "true").save("hdfs://big0.iie.org.mx:9000/JSGP/datasets/london/analytics/forecasting/meters/dar/"+meter+".csv")
    
        metrics_meter.loc[ct]=[meter,r2_win_narx,rmse_win_narx,mse_win_narx,mae_win_narx,r2_win_dar,rmse_win_dar,mse_win_dar,mae_win_dar]
        ct=ct+1
